1
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:45,000
ADAPTED FROM THE NOVEL HIDDEN LOVE BY ZHU YI

2
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,760
Is the tutor not here yet?

3
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:32,720
Or

4
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,480
is he already in Sang Yan's room?

5
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,480
He's not there.

6
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,920
Sang Yan, I want some instant noodles.

7
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,840
Add in two sausages and an egg!

8
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,680
The tutor that Mom mentioned

9
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,120
didn't come today, right?

10
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,440
That means he's late.

11
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:03,840
If that's the case,

12
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,680
his professional conduct is problematic.

13
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,120
You wouldn't be comfortable

14
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:09,960
with someone like that tutoring me, right?

15
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,440
So here's the deal.

16
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,160
Sang Yan.

17
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,960
How about you tell Mom

18
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,880
not to get me a tutor

19
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,680
during the New Year period?

20
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:24,080
Tutors are hard to find during this time anyway.

21
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,760
Let's talk about it after New Year.

22
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,440
Okay?

23
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,080
If you're willing to speak for me,

24
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,440
I'll give you 100 yuan this New Year.

25
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,560
How about 200 yuan then?

26
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,120
At most, five…

27
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,480
What are you yelling for in the morning?

28
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,880
That's Duan Jiaxu.

29
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,880
Didn't Mom tell you?

30
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,880
He's your tutor.

31
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:08,560
Nonsense!

32
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,880
How could you wake up so late?

33
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,400
He has been waiting all morning!

34
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:13,920
Lower your voice!

35
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,960
Keep it down!

36
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,480
Don't make me hit you!

37
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,959
Breakfast is ready.

38
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,600
Jiaxu.

39
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,280
There aren't enough eggs.

40
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,280
I'll add two more.

41
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:29,960
Sang Zhi.

42
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,160
Didn't you want instant noodles?

43
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,000
Two sausages and one egg.

44
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,520
Eat up. The noodles will get lumpy soon.

45
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,640
Got it.

46
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:49,760
An egg and two ham sausages.

47
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,560
You were sleeping so soundly just now.

48
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:17,040
Your brother couldn't even wake you up.

49
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,400
I stayed up too late last night

50
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,360
working on homework.

51
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,040
Is that so?

52
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,800
I thought you pretended not to hear him.

53
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:27,760
No, I really didn't hear him.

54
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,080
Next time…

55
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,720
I'll set off firecrackers at your door!

56
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,560
Here.

57
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:38,960
Thank you, Jiaxu.

58
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,600
Is it tasty?

59
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,080
Yes.

60
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,680
Here.

61
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,760
Have some more.

62
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:35,080
Have you been secretly practicing at home?

63
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,520
Do I even need to do that?

64
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,680
SOCCER FIELD

65
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,720
Sang Zhi.

66
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,200
Get out of the way!

67
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,400
Don't I have a tutoring session?

68
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,760
But we just finished breakfast!

69
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,520
Do your own reading first.

70
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,520
Am I the one getting tutored or are you?

71
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,400
Sang Zhi.

72
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,560
Go and take a rest first.

73
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:16,760
I'll come and tutor you

74
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:17,880
after this game, all right?

75
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:18,880
Sure.

76
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:27,080
Jiaxu, do you want some fruit?

77
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,040
No.

78
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:33,120
Just say so if you want some.

79
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,200
I'll cut it for you. Why all the hassle?

80
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,120
Don't be so mean to her all the time.

81
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,600
How do we beat this level?

82
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,560
Go to the left first.

83
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,440
Help me with this.

84
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,560
This is such a huge watermelon.

85
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,960
You won't be able to cut it using this.

86
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:50,080
It will work.

87
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,040
You can't cut it with this.

88
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,480
I've only been playing for a while.

89
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,520
Now I have to serve you.

90
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,440
I'm not cutting it!

91
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:58,040
-Sang Zhi. -I won't do it!

92
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,200
Take a look at this first.

93
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,440
I'll cut the watermelon after this game.

94
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,000
I thought you'd question my credentials.

95
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,440
After accepting this resume,

96
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,720
you're not allowed to replace me, okay?

97
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,280
Don't worry.

98
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,440
No one is willing to tutor her except you.

99
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,680
She has no other option but you.

100
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:19,040
"Duan Jiaxu."

101
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,280
So this is how you spell it.

102
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,200
Why didn't he attach his photo?

103
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,280
That's wrong.

104
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,840
Do we go to the right first?

105
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:27,960
Jump!

106
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:29,680
Awesome!

107
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,840
Okay, go up.

108
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,320
Isn't it upper right?

109
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,880
Should we go right or…

110
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,160
Lower right.

111
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:54,320
That's not it either.

112
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,840
Try upper left. Try it.

113
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,880
Go up?

114
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:05,800
Upper left.

115
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:09,120
We did it!

116
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:30,840
What were you photographing?

117
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,440
Me?

118
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,360
Him?

119
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,320
Why would you take his photo?

120
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,120
Is he as handsome as me?

121
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,200
Are you planning to show Mom and Dad

122
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,920
-that we're gaming? -I…

123
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,400
I'm not.

124
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:58,680
I just have a classmate

125
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:00,560
who said my brother is very handsome.

126
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,040
I can't show her a photo of you.

127
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,360
-It would be humiliating for me. -Hey!

128
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,920
I would prefer you rat us out!

129
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:06,920
Come back here!

130
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,240
Attention!

131
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,640
At ease!

132
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,920
She's simply impossible.

133
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,920
Try to understand her.

134
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,800
Kids her age

135
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,240
naturally have some sense of pride.

136
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,440
That's nonsense!

137
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,640
It's all your fault!

138
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,000
Come on. Let's continue.

139
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:53,160
CONTACT SETTINGS

140
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:55,160
NOTES AND TAGS SETTINGS

141
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:58,640
DUAN XX

142
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:05,120
CHAPTER FIVE, SECRETLY

143
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,520
THE NAME ENGRAVED IN MY HEART

144
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:16,600
NOTES AND LABELS SETTINGS

145
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:25,920
JIAXU

146
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,320
SAVING

147
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,600
JIAXU

148
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:46,720
Sang Zhi.

149
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,600
I've cut the watermelon for you.

150
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:00,920
Show me.

151
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,760
The photo you took just now.

152
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,600
What's wrong?

153
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:13,600
I want to check if it's ugly or not.

154
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,000
If so, you can snap a few more.

155
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,200
Didn't you say

156
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:20,080
that you want to show your classmate a handsome brother?

157
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,440
I can't make you look bad.

158
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,760
Don't we have a tutoring session?

159
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:26,800
Let's get on with it.

160
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:32,320
I'm eager to learn today.

161
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:35,440
And now you love learning?

162
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,760
Come, show me

163
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,880
your last physics final exam.

164
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,840
Did you not pay attention in class?

165
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:01,480
How could you get this question wrong?

166
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,400
I did pay attention.

167
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,600
I just didn't understand it.

168
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,560
This question on conservation of energy was a giveaway.

169
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,040
At first…

170
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:16,760
At first, I wanted to choose B.

171
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,160
That's right.

172
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:20,640
The correct answer is A.

173
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:28,480
Remember it.

174
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:31,120
Don't get problems on conservation of energy wrong again.

175
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:34,520
Maybe I didn't pay enough attention.

176
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,800
But even if I had paid full attention,

177
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:38,080
I wouldn't have understood it.

178
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,640
This is really difficult.

179
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,560
Didn't I tell you last time

180
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,720
to pay attention in class?

181
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,640
Have you forgotten?

182
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,240
That was such a long time ago.

183
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,560
Are you saying

184
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:50,240
that I need to remind you every day?

185
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:53,920
Can you?

186
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,000
Give me your physics book.

187
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,800
I'll start off with Ampère's Law.

188
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:07,240
Do you know the Left-Hand Rule?

189
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:10,920
Look.

190
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:14,080
Let's say there is a uniform magnetic field.

191
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:15,960
This is the direction of the current.

192
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,360
Now hold out your left hand.

193
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:49,080
Digest this first.

194
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:52,280
Work on this practice test.

195
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,240
I'll check it later.

196
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,480
I'll give you three lessons a week

197
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:00,160
during the winter break.

198
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,080
Is that too much for you?

199
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:08,720
No.

200
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,280
That's too little.

201
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,000
Can we have lessons every day?

202
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,800
I have my internship four days a week.

203
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:18,480
The remaining three days are all yours.

204
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:27,360
I thought you didn't want a tutor.

205
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,520
You're pretty good at teaching.

206
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,640
It's novel.

207
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:37,520
Of course.

208
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,120
You're unexpectedly eager to learn now.

209
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,120
Not bad.

210
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,600
Focus!

211
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,880
Next time,

212
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,640
I can explain

213
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:53,520
the Lorentz force to you.

214
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,000
By the way, Jiaxu.

215
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:01,160
Can I ask you a question?

216
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,280
Go ahead.

217
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,520
Why did you choose a university in Nanwu

218
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,040
instead of Yihe?

219
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,160
Isn't Yihe University also good?

220
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:16,840
I didn't want to stay in Yihe.

221
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:19,360
Isn't it nice to explore other places?

222
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,000
Why did you choose Nanwu then?

223
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,720
How do I put this?

224
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,720
My dream

225
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,800
is to eventually work in the gaming industry.

226
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,640
Nanwu is the city

227
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,760
with the biggest gaming industry.

228
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,920
That's why I came here.

229
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:40,440
What are you thinking about?

230
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:43,240
Hurry up and do your work.

231
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:19,880
Sorry, I'm late.

232
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:24,319
So have you digested what I taught you

233
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,440
in the last lesson?

234
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:30,240
Jiaxu, did you not sleep?

235
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,040
I was working late yesterday,

236
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:34,000
so I slept late.

237
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,280
Let's see.

238
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:41,600
Why don't I do my homework first?

239
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,880
You can check it after I'm done

240
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,480
and explain anything that is incorrect.

241
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:48,240
You have nothing to do while I work on it anyway,

242
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,000
so you can go and rest for a while.

243
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,880
What do you mean?

244
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,040
Are you trying to slack off?

245
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:54,920
Or will you tell on me to your parents

246
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,240
so that they can replace me?

247
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:57,320
That's not it.

248
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:01,560
I was just kidding. How about this?

249
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:03,240
You can

250
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:06,800
complete this set of problems.

251
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,480
I'll go over it with you when you're done.

252
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:12,520
Wake me up later.

253
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,480
I'm going to take a nap.

254
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,640
Are you slacking off?

255
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:41,920
What were you up to?

256
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,920
Slacking off.

257
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,720
Have you done the problems?

258
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,760
Show me

259
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:58,680
the set of problems you worked on over the weekend.

260
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,600
This problem.

261
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,280
You got it wrong.

262
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,960
The electric charge is negative.

263
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,240
So its direction of motion

264
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:25,040
is opposite to that of the current.

265
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,600
I guess I'm bad at tutoring.

266
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:32,720
You're getting worse.

267
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,720
Jiaxu.

268
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,480
Be more confident.

269
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:39,760
You've tutored me well.

270
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:42,600
I just can't remember very well

271
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,280
and I really don't understand it.

272
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:46,400
I just don't find physics interesting,

273
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,840
so it's hard for me to remember things.

274
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,280
What do you find interesting then?

275
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,720
In short, physics is boring.

276
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:15,000
I work so hard to tutor every day,

277
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,240
but you have a leisurely time.

278
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:18,360
Yes, it's your tutoring session, not mine!

279
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,080
Let me play a few rounds.

280
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:22,760
My legs!

281
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:23,880
Go away!

282
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:24,960
Get off!

283
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,360
Come on. Let's play together.

284
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,840
Airdrops! Go that way.

285
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,080
-I have something to tell you. -What is it?

286
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:34,480
Don't tell me you're quitting!

287
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,960
Don't be ridiculous.

288
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:38,480
I'm so good at tutoring.

289
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,600
I wanted to say that I want to take the kiddo

290
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:44,320
to the Science and Technology Museum in the city when we're all free.

291
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:45,720
Why?

292
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,640
She currently has no interest in physics

293
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:48,680
and can't learn.

294
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,680
So I thought that maybe a visit to the museum

295
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:53,960
might be able to pique her interest.

296
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,480
You're pretty responsible.

297
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,520
If I didn't know better,

298
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,120
I would think you were her brother.

299
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,840
Please also tell your parents for me.

300
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:02,960
No need.

301
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:04,680
They're very busy at the end of the year.

302
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:06,320
As her backup brother, I can decide.

303
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:09,280
When are we going?

304
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,560
I'll tell you when it's time.

305
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:13,320
-Hurry up! We're driving. -There's nobody around. Don't worry.

306
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:23,040
Have you been here before?

307
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:25,040
No.

308
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,400
This place is quite interesting.

309
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,240
I used to love coming here.

310
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,240
Only two tickets?
Are you not going in?

311
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,920
Only brats would visit a science museum.

312
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,200
Of course I'm not interested.

313
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:39,520
Who's the brat now?

314
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,080
That's enough.

315
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:46,040
I gave you money for three tickets.

316
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,400
Give me back my change.

317
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,840
I'll use it on games at the cybercafe.

318
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,560
I'll pick you guys up later. Bye!

319
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:55,920
How pretentious!

320
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:56,880
Let's go.

321
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:58,160
I'll show you around inside.

322
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,880
Don't you think this slide is interesting?

323
00:23:11,360 --> 00:23:13,320
There are a lot of physics concepts to it.

324
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,920
The reason that this slide is curved

325
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,560
instead of being a straight line

326
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:21,280
is based on the brachistochrone curve principle.

327
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,240
Therefore, although this slide looks high,

328
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:24,320
when you slide down,

329
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,920
you'll go fast in the middle portion,

330
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,360
then slow down toward the end.

331
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,200
That also makes it safer.

332
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,440
Do you want to try it out?

333
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:34,360
Go and have some fun.

334
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,320
Let's go!

335
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:47,880
How was it?

336
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:48,920
Was it fun?

337
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,960
Wasn't the middle section particularly exciting?

338
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:55,360
Yes, but it wasn't that fast.

339
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,360
That's the physics principle

340
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:58,560
that I just told you about.

341
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,760
Here's a bonus geographical fact for you.

342
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,640
The tsunami.

343
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,960
Did you know that the definition of a tsunami

344
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:12,000
is a catastrophic wave,

345
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:14,560
usually caused by an underwater earthquake?

346
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:17,720
It can reach a maximum wave speed

347
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,320
of over 700 km per hour.

348
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:21,680
Also, look at the waves.

349
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,760
They may be only 1 m high in the sea,

350
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,160
but when they reach the shore,

351
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,560
they can be tens of meters high.

352
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:29,000
Hence, it's a huge threat

353
00:24:29,080 --> 00:24:30,280
to cities by the sea.

354
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,320
What?

355
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:33,320
Run!

356
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:37,920
Hurry up, Jiaxu!

357
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,720
The tsunami is going to drown us!

358
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:40,800
How is that possible?

359
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,560
We've outrun the tsunami.

360
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,080
Come and try this out.

361
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:50,400
Put both your hands

362
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,240
on top of this flowerpot.

363
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:56,280
Look at the screen.

364
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,360
This is incredible!

365
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,200
This is thermoelectric sensing technology.

366
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,040
When the flowerpot senses your palm's temperature,

367
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:11,000
its thermoelectric sensor

368
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:12,960
will convert the change in temperature

369
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:14,680
into a change in power,

370
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:16,600
which triggers this animation.

371
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:18,720
-Look. -That's so cool.

372
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:20,680
The blooming flowers are attracting butterflies.

373
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,360
It's actually related to physics as well.

374
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:24,440
How amazing!

375
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:32,040
Here's my suggestion, Sang Zhi.

376
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:33,520
I know

377
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,120
you may have your personal preferences,

378
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:38,400
but try not to get sidetracked

379
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,760
and study hard.

380
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,800
It's because your future dreams

381
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,520
and the things you want to do in the future

382
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,080
will probably need to be achieved through studying.

383
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:51,800
Jiaxu.

384
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,840
I think you were probably very rebellious

385
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:55,080
when you were my age.

386
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,200
Why?

387
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:57,400
Because you play video games.

388
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:59,520
Does that make me rebellious?

389
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:01,400
My teacher said that we can't play video games.

390
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:05,320
When I was your age,

391
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:08,320
I would be overjoyed if I could play video games

392
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,680
for just one hour a week.

393
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:12,920
Those were the moments

394
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,760
when I could escape

395
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:18,520
from the negative realities of my life

396
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:19,800
by playing video games

397
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:20,880
and get a break.

398
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:31,840
Well,

399
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,680
I guess games

400
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:37,600
aren't that bad.

401
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,600
So,

402
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:44,080
you think video games can bring you

403
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:46,160
joy and comfort, right?

404
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,120
That's right.

405
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:50,440
Don't you find it very relaxing to play video games?

406
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:53,280
So at that time,

407
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:56,560
I dreamed of creating my own video game

408
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:59,360
and spreading joy to more people.

409
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,120
I'll study hard

410
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:14,120
and find my own dream.

411
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:17,520
But you have to work hard too, Jiaxu.

412
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:19,680
Because I think

413
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:24,560
you'll be able to achieve your dream soon.

414
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,760
Do you have such faith in me?

415
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,880
Let's work hard together then.

416
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,120
We can do it.

417
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:35,560
Okay!

418
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,120
Have some water.

419
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:13,280
I noticed you like to draw.

420
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:17,680
Drawing is a hobby that you can keep up.

421
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:20,680
It takes imagination to draw.

422
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,240
Besides,

423
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:25,200
I've always felt that people who like to draw

424
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:27,240
are full of kindness to the world.

425
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:30,120
They can record what they find beautiful in this world

426
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,560
through their paintbrush.

427
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,520
Jiaxu.

428
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,360
Can you not

429
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:39,600
be in a relationship?

430
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,120
What do you mean?

431
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,840
Don't you have a dream too?

432
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,080
If you get into a relationship,

433
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:56,240
you'll delay your dream.

434
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,920
I'm almost done with university.

435
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,720
Do I still need to avoid dating

436
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,120
for the sake of my studies?

437
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,560
Why don't you say this to your brother?

438
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:06,480
I…

439
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:11,240
I did.

440
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:12,440
What did he say?

441
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,880
He said, "Go away, little demon!"

442
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,520
I'm saying this

443
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,400
because my classmate's brother

444
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:21,840
had a girlfriend.

445
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:25,440
But that girl treated my classmate really badly.

446
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:27,120
How so?

447
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,600
I don't know.

448
00:29:29,160 --> 00:29:30,720
She treated your classmate badly?

449
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:33,400
Moreover,

450
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,360
if you have a girlfriend,

451
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:38,840
you won't be able to be so nice to me.

452
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:42,560
Now you realize that I'm nice to you.

453
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:46,440
Why are you thinking that far ahead?

454
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,320
If you don't see me for a couple of years,

455
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:49,800
you might forget all about me.

456
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:54,680
How about this then?

457
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:56,760
In the future,

458
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:58,920
I'll find a gentle girlfriend

459
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:00,480
who treats you well.

460
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,680
This way, you will have

461
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:04,680
one more person who is good to you.

462
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:05,600
All right?

463
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:17,240
Fine.

464
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:20,920
When you find one,

465
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:25,800
can you show her to me first?

466
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,240
Sure.

467
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:30,440
I'll show you when I find one.

468
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:34,320
I'll remember that.

469
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:46,400
Is there anything else you want to see?

470
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:48,200
Your brother is here.

471
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,040
Let's call it a day if you're tired.

472
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:51,960
Let's go.

473
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:56,600
Sang Yan!

474
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,000
-Hey. -What's wrong with you?

475
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:02,640
How was it?

476
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,600
Did you find the motivation to study?

477
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:08,920
Yes.

478
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:10,440
Well?

479
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:13,080
We went on a slide

480
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:14,680
and we went down like this.

481
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:16,440
-Weren't you there to learn? -Hello, Li Xun?

482
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:18,200
-It also lit up. -I've modified that.

483
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:20,400
-I sent it to you this morning. -And there was water.

484
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,840
-A water screen. -Does it need more revisions?

485
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:25,520
-Were you just playing around? -Okay, I have my laptop with me.

486
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,800
I'll find a place to do the revisions and send it to you.

487
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:29,600
-Okay, bye. -I'm only telling you what I saw.

488
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:33,160
Take your sister home first.

489
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:34,960
I'm going to do some work over there.

490
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,400
Okay.

491
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:39,000
Remember what I told you today.

492
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,920
-Go home. -Do you need a ride?

493
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:42,880
No, thank you.

494
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,680
Here, put on your ugly hat.

495
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,200
Where's the strap?

496
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:57,760
Go away!

497
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:04,200
Stupid little demon, I'm so nice to you

498
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:05,600
and you didn't even wait for me.

499
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:16,520
Sang Yan!

500
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:20,120
My sketchbook is missing.

501
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,920
It's that book that I usually draw in.

502
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:24,280
There was nothing in the car just now.

503
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:26,480
Are you sure? Take me there and show me.

504
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:27,400
Let's go!

505
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:28,840
There's really nothing there.

506
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:30,400
I've told you.

507
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:32,240
Just buy another one if you've lost it.

508
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:35,200
Are you sure you've checked everywhere?

509
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:36,440
Yes!

510
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:42,000
From the Science and Technology Museum

511
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:44,440
to here.

512
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:45,440
The car.

513
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:47,080
My room.

514
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:01,600
The museum.

515
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:14,720
Hello.

516
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:17,160
I visited the Science and Technology Museum today

517
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:19,560
and accidentally left my sketchbook there.

518
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,080
It's a green sketchbook.

519
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,600
Did you pick it up?

520
00:33:22,680 --> 00:33:23,800
Yes.

521
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:30,040
We passed it to the boy who was with you.

522
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:31,320
Did he not give it to you?

523
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:39,240
PURE MILK

524
00:33:39,320 --> 00:33:41,480
SLEEPY

525
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:52,840
What should I do if Jiaxu sees it?

526
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,920
Little demon, I have your sketchbook.

527
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:11,280
-I'm tossing it if you don't want it. -Give it to me!

528
00:34:13,679 --> 00:34:14,880
Duan Jiaxu dropped it off

529
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:16,000
on his way to work.

530
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:18,320
Did he look inside?

531
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,719
How would I know?

532
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,239
Why didn't you ask him?

533
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:25,679
Is there anything shady in there?

534
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:26,800
No.

535
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:29,120
Fine. I'm going back to sleep.

536
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:48,000
He could've just called me.

537
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,880
Why did he ask Sang Yan to pass it to me?

538
00:34:52,199 --> 00:34:55,880
Doesn't that mean he has looked inside

539
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,160
and felt awkward?

540
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:00,560
That's why he didn't give it to me himself!

541
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:11,560
Then what if…

542
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:29,800
Why are you back?

543
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,720
I can't stand it at home.

544
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:36,200
Did you come back to keep me company?

545
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,920
By the way, Jiaxu, listen.

546
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:39,600
Don't come on Tuesday.

547
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:40,680
Come on Thursday instead.

548
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,640
Why?

549
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:43,040
The little demon has puppy love.

550
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:45,880
I gave her an earful and confiscated her phone and laptop.

551
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:47,480
She won't be in the mood to study,

552
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:48,400
so forget it.
Puppy love?

553
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,440
Is it with that classmate of hers?

554
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:55,320
No, it's online dating! Can you believe it?

555
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:57,000
What?

556
00:35:57,080 --> 00:35:58,880
That's right. She told me herself.

557
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:01,200
All right, I'll come next week then.

558
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:06,080
It's normal for her to experience this

559
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:07,160
at her age.

560
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:09,160
Anyway, just talk some sense into her

561
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:10,880
and make sure she knows the limits.

562
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,480
I'm sure she will get it.

563
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,200
Guess what?

564
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,720
I don't care about other people.

565
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:18,360
But it's not allowed for my sister!

566
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:20,160
They must break up

567
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,000
or I'll beat that guy up!

568
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:05,320
He should alreadyknow

569
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:08,240
about the online dating story that I made up.

570
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,240
How should I face him

571
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,880
during our lesson later?

572
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:16,360
He will no longer think

573
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:18,360
that I drew him, right?

574
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:21,720
How should a heartbroken person look like?

575
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,680
Should I act sad,

576
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:26,160
upset, and miserable?

577
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:31,000
Will he not believe it?

578
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,040
-Or should I-- -Little demon!

579
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,280
Little demon!

580
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:38,640
Little demon.

581
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,120
How have you been

582
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:53,400
these past few days?

583
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:04,360
I'll take you for a ride

584
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:05,640
when you finish your lesson.

585
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,120
I won't tell Mom and Dad.

586
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:13,560
I don't want to be scolded either.

587
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:40,120
I heard from your brother

588
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:42,360
that you're dating online.

589
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,600
How did you meet him?

590
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:47,640
Tell me.

591
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:52,400
You don't have to be so nosy.

592
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,640
What's wrong with caring about you?

593
00:38:56,720 --> 00:38:58,400
You asked me not to date,

594
00:38:58,480 --> 00:38:59,840
but you did it yourself.

595
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:02,880
From what he said,

596
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:05,320
he likely believes that the one I like

597
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:07,680
is the non-existent online friend.

598
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:09,520
So was it your young boyfriend

599
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:10,840
who asked you to meet him?

600
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:20,560
How old is he?

601
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,880
He's graduating from university soon.

602
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:29,880
How old did you say he was?

603
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:33,200
Twenty-something.

604
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:40,760
Where did he tell you to meet him?

605
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:44,080
In Yihe.

606
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:53,400
Sang Zhi.

607
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:54,960
Tell me.

608
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:57,360
Does your old boyfriend

609
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:59,440
know how old you are?

610
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:14,000
What's his phone number?

611
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:19,200
Are you covering up for him?

612
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:25,280
Sang Zhi.

613
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,520
I don't want to lose my temper with you,

614
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:29,240
but you need to know that

615
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:31,160
your family has your best interests at heart.

616
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:33,040
They won't let you date online

617
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:35,200
because they believe it will harm you.

618
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,000
You can't be in a relationship

619
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:39,240
until you graduate from high school and become an adult.

620
00:40:40,200 --> 00:40:42,000
Once you're in college,

621
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:43,280
you can do whatever you want.

622
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:44,760
No one will stop you.

623
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:46,480
Do you hear me?

624
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:55,280
But I can't resist the temptation.

625
00:42:44,160 --> 00:42:47,000
SLEEPY
